---
// movie-tracking.astro - Project detail page for the Movie Tracking app
// This is equivalent to your Flask project_movie-tracking.html template
//
// URL: /projects/movie-tracking
// (because this file is at src/pages/projects/movie-tracking.astro)
//
// NOTE: In your Flask app, each project had its own template with hardcoded content.
// We're doing the same here - one .astro file per project.
// For many projects, you could use dynamic routing with [slug].astro + markdown files.

import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Import project data to get the project info
import projects from '../../data/projects.json';

// Find this specific project from the array
// .find() is like a Python list comprehension: [p for p in projects if p.slug == 'movie-tracking'][0]
const project = projects.find((p) => p.slug === 'movie-tracking');

// If project not found, redirect to 404 (safety check)
if (!project) {
  return Astro.redirect('/404');
}
---

<BaseLayout title={`${project.name} | William Hu`}>
  <main class="main main--project">
    <div>
      <!--
        Hero image:
        Flask: src="{{ url_for('static', filename=project['hero']) }}"
        Astro: src={`/${project.hero}`}
      -->
      <img
        class="hero"
        src={`/${project.hero}`}
        alt="A hand holding a pen, about to write something in a project planner."
      />

      <article class="project">
        <article class="project__main">
          <!--
            Project title:
            Flask: {{ project['name'] }}
            Astro: {project.name}
          -->
          <h2 class="project__heading">{project.name}</h2>

          <h3>Overview</h3>
          <p>
            This app was designed to meet the specific needs of tracking and managing TV series and movies.
            It offers comprehensive and detailed recording and categorization capabilities,
            focusing on aspects such as OTT platforms, countries, actors and more.
          </p>
          <p>
            The architecture of the app is designed to ensure efficient database management, tracking and recording viewing habits.
          </p>

          <h3>Features</h3>
          <article>
            <ul>
              <li class="main__section">
                <div class="main__section-title">Comprehensive Media Categories and Description</div>
                <div class="main__section-imagegroup">
                  <img src="/img/content/f1.jpg" alt="Feature 1" />
                  <img src="/img/content/f2.jpg" alt="Feature 2" />
                </div>
                <section class="main__section-content">
                  <p>
                    First, the homepage is divided into Shows, Movies, Upcoming Shows, and Upcoming Movies, allowing
                    users to easily see the information, ratings and upcoming releases.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    User can also view detailed media description, including posters, OTT platforms, cast lists, release date and regions and more.
                  </p>
                </section>
              </li>

              <li class="main__section">
                <div class="main__section-title">Customized Watchlists, Ratings, and Viewing Statistics</div>
                <div class="main__section-imagegroup">
                  <img src="/img/content/f8.jpg" alt="Feature 8" />
                  <img src="/img/content/f3.jpg" alt="Feature 3" />
                </div>
                <section class="main__section-content">
                  <p>
                    The app offers a service to add unwatched media to a watchlist and allows users to rate each movie they have already seen.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    Additionally, the app automatically ranks actors based on the number of times they have appeared in the movies one have watched.
                  </p>
                </section>
              </li>

              <li class="main__section">
                <div class="main__section-title">Dynamic Calendar View for Watched and Upcoming Media</div>
                <div class="main__section-imagegroup">
                  <img src="/img/content/f4.jpg" alt="Feature 4" />
                </div>
                <section class="main__section-content">
                  <p>
                    A scrollable calendar view presents daily viewing records and
                    detailed information about upcoming movies, allowing users to
                    easily navigate through their watch history and future releases.
                  </p>
                </section>
              </li>

              <li class="main__section">
                <div class="main__section-title">Accurate Viewing Time Statistics</div>
                <div class="main__section-imagegroup">
                  <img src="/img/content/f5.jpg" alt="Feature 5" />
                  <img src="/img/content/f6.jpg" alt="Feature 6" />
                  <img src="/img/content/f7.jpg" alt="Feature 7" />
                </div>
                <section class="main__section-content">
                  <p>
                    The app provides precise statistics on daily, monthly, and yearly viewing times,
                    as well as comparisons of viewing times across different streaming platforms.
                  </p>
                </section>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <h3>Architecture</h3>
          <ol>
            <li>
              <p>Data Management</p>
              <p>MySQL is used as a local database for storing and manipulating data.
                For example, rating media, tracking viewing habits, and organizing playlists and more.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>Call SQL query in SwiftUI</p>
              <p>Write SQL queries in JavaScript so that I can leverage its flexibility as the intermediary between the app and database, to handle database operation in SwiftUI.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>Fetch media information from website</p>
              <p>The app integrates with the TMDB API to fetch a wide range of media content from the <a class="tmdb__link" href="https://www.themoviedb.org/" target="_blank">The Movie Database website.</a></p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </article>

        <section class="project__side-section">
          <article class="project__meta-group">
            <h3 class="project__heading project__heading--meta">Technologies</h3>

            <ul class="technology-list">
              <li class="technology-list__item">SwiftUI</li>
              <li class="technology-list__item">Express.js</li>
              <li class="technology-list__item">MySQL</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
